javadoc:
A generic data type used by table models in order to signal that the data should render
 a preview for a given {@link ProgramLocation}, where the preview is what is displayed in 
 the Listing.

methods.name: <init>

params.name: codeUnitFormat
params.comment: the format needed to render preview data

methods.javadoc:
Get the preview for the code unit at or containing the address associated with this cell's row.
@return the preview string.
methods.name: getDisplayString
methods.comment: Get the preview for the code unit at or containing the address associated with this cell's row.

methods.javadoc:
Get the preview as HTML for the code unit at or containing the address associated with this cell's row.
@return the preview string.
methods.name: getHTMLDisplayString
methods.comment: Get the preview as HTML for the code unit at or containing the address associated with this cell's row.
